The other 4 largest countries, South Korea, Kazakhstan, Brazil and Taiwan all had boom years.

South Korea is the home of chaebol conglomerates whose workforces account for one out of 6 people each in the nation. Kazakhstan and Brazil saw all-time highs in oil and commodity steroids prices, while Taiwan was driven largely by the mighty Haswell processor from Intel. The next 4 largest countries our entries, but they are significantly behind the 5 largest. Lithuania and Belarus both had growth near 10%, and Russia and Mongolia both grew by 8%.

We have long seen a breakdown of the titans of the 90's and technology has triggered the major changes that we are seeing today. This breakdown has streamlined distribution, created more competitive services and forced consolidation on players that previously might have had a relatively competitive hold on the premium design markets (most prominently Nokia, HTC and Sony Ericsson).
